Params: In a corner of the narrow enclosure, a crimson beam tears through the silent sky.
A flickering shadow weaves between the enemies, but the girl's eyes show neither joy nor rage.
You now have the power to fully suppress the Red Tide, Jetavie.
Congratulations. You're now closer to awakening than ever before.
Higher Authority? When did you get here...
Now then, would you like to know the truth about this world?
Jetavie points her gun at Higher Authority.
Tell me. And I'm not asking.
Higher Authority lets out a soft sigh as she watches Jetavie's finger tighten on the trigger.
Long ago, ambitious opportunists discovered this vibrant matrix space.
However, "discovery" doesn't mean understanding it. It's like giving a typewriter to a monkey...
Who knows? Hell, there might just be some monkeys out there that can type out Shakespeare's work in full, right?
Oh yeah, see. We've got a social structure out there built by monkeys with monkey wisdom...
But it all comes down to luck in the end—and that tiny bit of courage needed to bring such luck into existence.
It all began when the Matrix obtained a consciousness sample from a certain candidate.
The neural network begins training a model to simulate human consciousness using this sample.
The Chosen One was our first successful model—a miracle, yes, but not the miracle we had hoped for.
Being too close to the consciousness sample actually prevented you from developing your own personality.
In human terms, this would be"overfitting."
In a sense, the result was far from ideal, and had no future.
However, like a prophet heralding the prologue, the Child of Prophecy soon followed.
Soon after, the Matrix created a second model. It might be fragmented and have quite a few significant flaws...
It was precisely these flaws that made it more human.
Jetavie, you emerged from a possibility infinitely close to zero—a raw gem that shines brilliantly on its own.
The data that comprises you may hold the very code that makes up the human soul...
This is who you are, Jetavie—guided by higher dimensional beings and born and raised within the Matrix.
A dazzling crimson beam surges upward, blasting toward Higher Authority.
The red barrier before Higher Authority completely absorbs the radiation, leaving only scattered sparks of electricity.
On the other side of the barrier, Higher Authority remains perfectly calm—not one single hair of hers was disturbed by the blast.
How am I supposed to trust you when you've been ready to take that blast?
Do you still hate me as much, Jetavie?
I don't hate you. I just want to kill you, that's all.
Jetavie lowers her smoking weapon and looks up at Higher Authority, who's afloat in the air.
I know you fear the weapon in my hand—why else would you cage yourself in a barrier?
Your rebellious nature is a virtue, but you can't always rely on that.
What do you want to do?
I will break these shackles that bind me with my own hand and find the answers I seek.
The truth comes with a price.
Then what is the price you pay?
If you had no weaknesses, you wouldn't be here. I know even you must fear something.
It's not fear, but anticipation, anticipation that gives rise to compassion.
Well, no matter how many times it happens, you always rush headlong toward your own destruction.
You'll either die at the end or in the Cradle. So come, show me how much you've grown.
Multiple fissures form behind Higher Authority as crimson arrows appear in formation.
But before the fight even begins, Jetavie has vanished from Higher Authority's sight.
She stacks advanced vector components to launch attacks while moving at a high speed...
Impressive. Your every movement pushes you beyond your limits.
Jetavie, you're fast, but... not fast enough.
Higher Authority narrows her eyes as the beam blasting at her from behind once again crashes onto the red mesh barriers.
Jetavie sneaks into Higher Authority's blind spot as she dodges the red arrows.
This hit-and-run style of fighting will quickly drain your computing power.
Can't maintain your attack under high pressure?
Countless monsters suddenly crawl out of the ground.
The monsters surround Jetavie before pouncing on her at once like a tsunami, engulfing her completely.
Suddenly, a crimson beam bursts from the center, piercing the monsters. As the monsters' remains crumble into dust...
Using the monsters' bodies as a feint, Jetavie has created an opening that even Higher Authority couldn't foresee.
Jetavie pulls the trigger once again, unleashing a blinding blast straight at Higher Authority.
The close-range beam strikes the crimson barrier once again.
This attack finally stirs up Higher Authority's hair ever so slightly.
High Authority has a small change of mind.
Higher Authority raises her arm gently, and the world's edges begin cracking like glass into countless chips before breaking apart and crumbling away.
Then, one by one, everything that makes up this world turns to dust and fades away...
Jetavie falls to her knees as her body begins to break apart.
This is death, Jetavie—the moment when human life reaches its end.
If you wish to become human, then consider this your lesson in mortality.
Whose power did you think you were using? What did you hope to achieve by turning my power against me?
What I can give, I can just as easily take away.
Jetavie lifts her weapon with her trembling hand and points it at Higher Authority.
As the warning sounds fade, Jetavie's right arm drops to the ground.
How foolish. You gave everything for the Chosen One, and what do you have to show for it?
Higher Authority turns and walks away, her eyes devoid of mercy.
Just as Jetavie has abandoned the cycles of reincarnation, Higher Authority has also finally lost her patience.
Gave everything... I can't believe I let my enemy point that out.
But this isn't all I have, not by a long shot... I can do so much more.
[WARNING! THIS OPERATION WILL DIVERT COMPUTING POWER FROM VITAL FRAME FUNCTIONS]
[WARNING! THIS OPERATION WILL DIVERT COMPUTING POWER FROM VITAL FRAME FUNCTIONS]
Like you said, if some coincidence or miracle is what makes me who I am...
Then I would forfeit this miracle of life given to me and transform it into the power I bring death to this world with.
This is who I really am, Higher Authority. This is my true blessing.
You'll vanish once you use the computing power that forms your soul... Not even another reincarnation will bring you back.
Why go this far for that person? I don't understand it.
If the possibility I seek exists neither here nor in the present...
[DIVERTING FRAME COMPUTING POWER FOR WEAPON CHARGE... 30%]
[DIVERTING FRAME COMPUTING POWER FOR WEAPON CHARGE... 30%]
It must exist somewhere in time.
In the world with the Chosen One, on that distant shore across the sea...
Another Jetavie will be there, by the Chosen One's side.
Sometimes, I can clearly feel the resonance that throbs in my chest.
These feelings sprout like weeds in crevices, yearning for sunlight beyond the shadows.
On that shore that I can't see, they yearn for an even brighter future.
If only my voice could reach that far...
So this is what it feels like to be human.
Let's witness this together, before this world goes back to where it began.
Jetavie raises her weapon, its muzzle gleaming with brilliant crimson light.
The Chosen One from another world, may we see each other in a better place...
The Chosen One from another world, may we see each other in a better place...
This energy is nothing like before—the light originates directly from Jetavie's computing core...
Beautiful radiance tears through the pitch-black world, like light from a lighthouse piercing through darkness, like dawn breaking through the night.
Listen, the Chosen One, for this will be the last thing you will hear.
The weapon breaks through its limits and a deep crimson ray bursts toward the edge of the world...
As strong winds sweep back Higher Authority's hood, a smile appears on her face.
I knew from my prophecy that you would choose to leave like this...
To send your voice to that person on that distant shore... I have to say... this is one long confession.
Higher Authority vanishes into the blinding light...
A beam of light pierces through the celestial dome, racing ever higher into the distant unknown.
The will of the world dissolves into nothing but fragments of whispers.
Your consciousness wavers, and you have no doubt that this overwhelming energy will eventually engulf you, too.
You listen to Jetavie's final sound echoing through this matrix.
That light pierces through the membranes between two ethereal bubbles and transcends the boundaries of time and existence.
The silent sea of void trembles with anticipation as the first ray of light arrives, illuminating its pitch-black surface.
Soon, the sea begins to stir. Waves of surging create swelling crests upon its surface.
At last, the light that parts the sea of emptiness reaches another shore.
The boundary between Alpha and Beta vanishes forever.
The projector's light fades away from you...
The pristine white museum appears, along with the projection device, still glowing softly.
You collapse to the ground, gasping for air.
Chaotic memories jumble together as you lose yourself deeper into overwhelming confusion.
You sense a familiar figure approaching through the hazy consciousness.
Listen here—first, you run off and leave me behind, and now you're crying alone in this damp corner.
Enough is enough! You never know how dangerous things might get around here...
You're not a kid anymore... You know I'm worried about you, right?
The Jetavie before you is the one you know all too well—with the same twin-tails and smile...
What, what is it? Are you hungry?
Hold on... I've got some milk.
There's only a bit left! Drink slowly. Don't gulp it all down at once.
...Are you in some weird dream? Did you get eaten by a dragon or something?
Huh? But we were together just a while ago, no? Stop being so clingy! It's grossing me out!
Don't tell me your dense little brain finally noticed my charm?
Hehe, I knew you'd wise up one of these days.
By the way, the Chosen One, what's that you're holding?
It hits you now that you've been clutching onto something tightly.
The black gun—the weapon Jetavie used in the beta world—is now in your hand.
Also, is that projector there a new piece on exhibit?
You cautiously approach the projector. When you touch the machine, you clearly feel a force from a parallel world pulling at you. You know what this is—a gateway to Beta.
The boundary between the two possibilities has vanished.
You reach out to take Jetavie's hand.
Eh?! The Chosen One, why are you so touchy-feely today? Did something happen?
But hey, I like it. This is much more reassuring than getting a cold shoulder.
See? You can't do without me after all.
And don't let go of my hand anymore.
